      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RISING REVOLUTION (6) resumes from a lengthy break. Stalked the speed on debut in the small field with a respectable third to Jellicious over 1100m at this track last September. Expected to have strengthened over the break and finished seventh in a recent trial at Rosehill over 900m. Lugging bit goes on and shapes as a top-three contender. MIND YA BIZZ (4) returns for her third preparation. Bumped into a couple of handy types when last in work. Primed with the two trials on her home track. Conditions suit and can overcome the sticky gate. STARDUST MEMORIES (7) started hard in the market on debut ($1.90 fav), when she came out quickly but was a spent force in the straight finishing fifth over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Deserves another chance after the two slick trial wins. HO ALOHA (3) no excuses today in this harder race fifth-up. Ran on late in the heavy (10) going to secure second over 1100m at Nowra. Has the pace to get over from the sticky gate.",
